Fit at Forty
Our weekly LIVE! 

If you follow me and @gulpanag you probably know we are both fitness enthusiasts. But we struggle with staying motivated just like everyone else. So how do we continue despite our bad days and what keeps us from giving up? 
Sharing our insights with each other has benefited us as friends to grow in our journey and learn much from one another.
I hope our conversations resonate with you and benefit you in some way to stay disciplined.
Thanks for tuning in and for those who missed the live I hope you enjoy watching the chat.

We would love to know what other topics you’d like us to discuss in the comments below.

#friends #live #conversations #fitness #fitatforty #exercise #workout #shruphotodiary

A gentle reminder of who you are. 

The world has been benefitting from making us forget who we are. We are constantly being made to feel like we lack in some way or another, so we keep consuming to feel whole and someone keeps getting richer at our expense. 

But you are not your income or your job. You are not a bank balance, a house, riches, holidays, a car, a watch, a bag, a follower count. 

You are every drop of rain. Every sunset. Every flowing river. Every blossom. Every rainbow. Every act of kindness you bestow upon someone. Every warm hug that makes someone feel safe. Every word of assurance you gift to someone else. You’re the love that makes people feel their inner light. 

You’re part of a consciousness that cannot be reduced to a price tag or a product. 
You’re one with the universe. Start acting like it.

Stop playing small.
#rememberwhoyouare #awaken #wisdom #consciousness #shruphotodiary

latestPosts.caption:
*Upgraded my operating system this solstice*
If mid april someone had said you’ll be back on a plane before you know it, I would’ve laughed. Or cried actually. 

The degree of pain that I was enduring was something I’ve never encountered. It was relentless. Persistent. Omnipresent. 

I just wanted anything to make it stop. 

So, I stopped all my pain medication and just let the pain surge.
I screamed and howled in agony. 
My doctor and I decided it was the only way to track my healing. (Without numbing)

But no matter what my situation was, I went to physiotherapy every alternate day.

I didn’t get attached to the pain or the relief. I just felt whatever came in the moment, knowing it would soon disappear. 

Then on 19th May I watched, mission impossible and Tom Cruise said “remember it’s only pain” and that changed something :)

It was just pain.

I kept doing whatever my physiotherapist said, without debate. I chose to believe her instead of the internet.
I trusted the process and it worked. 

I’m still healing but now I’m a new version of myself. 
Brave. Strong. Resilient. Fearless. 

The first half of 2025 has been a real life test of all that I have studied in the past 5 years. 
The non attachment and impermanence from my Buddhist studies, showing up doing the work and trusting the process from my Arts Based therapy and living in the present moment, from my mindfulness meditation teacher’s training. 
So far I seem to be fairing well. 

I hope the second half of the year rewards me with miracles and paradise. I’m not accepting anything else.

Also I’m taking the slow road. To everywhere and everything. 

#version2.0 #newandimproved #healing #backinjury #lessons #mentalwellnesscoach #shruphotodiary

I was honoured to share my story with everyone present and I hope that I was able to inspire people to make their health their number one priority. (Despite my hoarse inaudible voice ;)

Grateful to @theeventalist.in @madhat.in @sylvioolvin_music @aviralkaushik_  for being so gracious & patient with me and my multiple health scenarios that caused last minute panic. Hope to work with your team again. 

This was my first work assignment since my back injury and it was destined to be on yoga day! My practice has always been my saviour and my sanctuary. 🥰❤️

We’re thrilled to introduce the Narrative Jury for KASHISH 2025 – a powerhouse panel of industry veterans and storytellers 🎬🌈

Together, they will form the jury responsible for selecting winners 🏅 across 5 prestigious awards categories at the festival.

🎬 Meet the Narrative Jury:
🌟 #ShishirSharma – A veteran of stage and screen, Shishir has brought powerful performances to theatre, television, films like Raazi and Dangal, and acclaimed digital series.

🌟 @shru2kill – Beloved for her roles in Shararat and Fanaa, Shruti now also champions mental wellness as a certified arts-based therapy and mindfulness practitioner.

🌟 @tanuja__chandra – Known for strong, character-driven stories like Dushman and Qarib Qarib Singlle, Tanuja is a celebrated filmmaker and writer with a distinct voice.

With their wealth of experience and unique perspectives, this dynamic jury is all set to spotlight bold, heartfelt, and boundary-pushing narratives at KASHISH 2025.
We can’t wait to see which stories shine through! 🌟📽️🌈

A moment that sparkled with soul at Sunshine Festival 7!

When the radiant Shruti Seth graced us as our Chief Guest, the energy shifted—hearts opened, smiles bloomed, and magic unfolded.

She met our healers, embraced the vibe, and shared wisdom that felt like a warm hug to every soul present.

Thank you, Shruti, @shru2kill for being YOU—grounded, glowing, and deeply inspiring.

This reel? It’s a love letter to that unforgettable day.

#sunshinefestival7 #shrutiseth

“You are here to witness your child’s life — not live it for them.”

In this week’s episode, I sit down with the incredible Shruti Seth — actor, mother, and mental wellness coach — for one of the most raw, honest, and moving conversations we’ve had on the show.

If you’ve ever felt overwhelmed, stretched thin, or just wanted to parent more consciously — this episode is for you.
